Key Match Events: Adam Zampa's all-round performance with 29 runs off 19 balls and bowling figures of 3/21 was crucial in Australia's victory.
Marnus Labuschagne scored 71 runs off 83 balls, contributing significantly to Australia's total.
Chris Woakes took 4 wickets for 54 runs in 9.3 overs for England.
Ben Stokes scored 64 runs off 90 balls for England.
Adil Rashid's quickfire 20 runs off 15 balls and his bowling figures of 2/38 in 10 overs were notable.
Pat Cummins took 2 wickets for 49 runs in 10 overs for Australia.
England's chase faltered with the early dismissal of Jonny Bairstow on the first ball of the innings.
Australia's ninth-wicket stand was pivotal in their victory.
England were officially knocked out of contention for the semi-finals with this loss.
Post-Match Reflections: Jos Buttler expressed disappointment and acknowledged that England did not do themselves justice in the tournament.
Pat Cummins praised his team's performance and highlighted the improvement in their fielding and the contributions of different match-winners.
Adam Zampa reflected on his performance, emphasizing his strategy of attacking the stumps and staying positive while batting.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was held at Narendra Modi Stadium, Ahmedabad.
Australia won by 33 runs, moving closer to the semi-finals.
England's defeat marked their sixth loss in seven games, ending their title defense in the World Cup.
